    "(70)Here we have introduced the index notation i, j for single-particle states that are occupied in |ψ 0 ⟩, and m, n denote states that are empty in |ψ 0 ⟩.",
    "( 70) is called the Thouless parametrization of Slater determinants [220].We now promote the coefficients z im (t) to general time-dependent functions, with the time evolution determined by the Time-Dependent Variational Principle (TDVP).",
    "In general, consider the LagrangianL = i 2 ⟨ψ| ψ⟩ -⟨ ψ|ψ⟩ ⟨ψ|ψ⟩ - ⟨ψ|H|ψ⟩ ⟨ψ|ψ⟩,(71)and the time-evolution of |ψ⟩ from the variational optimization of the Lagrangian.If the variational manifold of |ψ⟩ is the entire Hilbert space, the above procedure reproduces the exact Schrödinger time-evolution.",
    "More generally, in the TDVP, we can restrict the variational manifold of |ψ⟩ to a more tractable sub-manifold of the Hilbert space.",
    "For our present purposes, we use |ψ(z(t))⟩ as an ansatz to approximate the exact time-evolved state e -iHt |ψ(z(0))⟩."
